AGI - Israeli defence forces have recovered the bodies of three other Hamas hostages in the north of the Gaza Strip in a night operation. The same IDF did. It is Orión Hernàndez Radoux, 30 years old, Hanan Yablonka, 42 years old, and Michel Nisenbaum, 59 years old. the three would have been killed on October 7, according to sources of "reliable intelligence". Until recently they had no information about their state and they believed they were alive, writes the Israeli press. The three bodies were found in the Mefalsim area, the same place where Hamas terrorists kidnapped and killed four other hostages whose bodies were recovered last week in a tunnel in Jabaliya. Hernàndez Radoux, a French-Ministerian citizen, was Shani Louk's boyfriend, one of the four hostages found last week. Hernàndez Radoux and Yablonka - together with Louk and two other hostage bodies recovered last week - were at the music festival Supernova near the border community of Rèim during the October 7 attack. They fled to Mefalsim where they were murdered.
&nbsp;
The IDF states that the bodies of the three hostages were recovered in a joint operation conducted by the military and Shin Bet, following the analysis of the "precise information" obtained in recent days. After the bodies were identified during the night at the Abu Kabir Forensic Institute, their families were informed by military representatives, adds the IDF.&nbsp;
