AGI - More than 20 people were arrested in connection with the terrorist attack in the municipality of Crocus, Russia. The SBB Director Alexander Bortnikov said this at a meeting of the Board of Heads of Security Agencies and Special Services of the CSI Member States in Bishkek. According to the head of the SBB, "it can already be said with certainty that the Ukrainian military intelligence is directly linked to the terrorist attack." "We are currently identifying the entire circle of people involved in the crime, more than 20 people have already been arrested, including direct authors and accomplices," Bortnikov said. According to the head of the SBB, reports Ria Novosti, two of the four participants in the attack had arrived in Russia from Turkey shortly before the attack. One of the detainees admitted he arrived on March 4 and would receive a bid of half a million rubles to kill people. Another defendant, Faridun Shamsiddin, published photos of Istanbul on Instagram in February. Eight photographs are dated 23 February, almost all contain geolocation, "Aksaray, Istanbul". These include a picture of the same Shamsiddin and allegedly filmed at the Fatih Mosque. As a result of the investigation, it emerged that the preparation, financing, attack and withdrawal of terrorists were coordinated via the Internet by militants of the Vilayat Khorasan group of the Afghan-Pakistana area, added Bortnikov. "At the end of the attack, the terrorists received the clear order to move to the Ukrainian border, where on that side a window was prepared," said the head of the SBB. The director of the SBB added that it can already be said with certainty that the Ukrainian military intelligence is directly linked to the terrorist attack. "I want to ensure that all the circumstances of the crime will be ascertained and that all the people involved will not escape punishment," he concluded. The attack took place on the evening of March 22 in the concert hall Crocus City Hall in Krasnogorsk. Several men broke into the building, shot firefight and fired fire bombs. According to the latest data from the Ministry of Emergency Situations, 145 people died in the attack and more than 500 were wounded.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
<div </div
<br> Supporting that "preparing, financing, attack and withdrawal of terrorists were coordinated via the Internet by members of the Khorasan Province group", Afghan branch of Isis, Moscow confirms that behind the attack there is the coordination of the Islamist group, but continues to reiterate thesis of the Ukrainian direction. Although the attack on the Crocus was immediately claimed by the jihadist organization of the Islamic State, Russian authorities continued to see the hand of Ukraine, while Kiev has always categorically refused any involvement. At the end of March, Russian President Vladimir Putin admitted that the attack had been committed by "radical Islamists", but continued to make it clear that the sponsor was Kiev. The same head of the SBB reiterated the alleged role of Ukrainian intelligence. "The investigation continues, but we can already say for sure that the Ukrainian military intelligence is directly involved in the attack," he said.
