AGI -&nbsp;Donald&nbsp;Trump&nbsp; has evoked the possibility that migrants who enter clandestinely in the United States want to create an "army" and attack Americans "from within", "taking cities". The tycoon launched this message during the busy rally in the Bronx, New York, where, according to the organizers, at least twenty thousand people arrived to listen to it.
&nbsp;
"I'm not only talking about South American countries - Trump said - we talk about African countries. Twenty-two people arrived the other day from the Congo. Where are you from? And they answered: 'from prison, but now we won't tell you we're happy to be here'." "They come from Africa - he continued - come from Asia, come from all over the world. They come from the Middle East, from Yemen, and we are bombing Yemen, and they come to us." "And if you look at these people - he continued - you see that they are all physically fit, and that they are between 19 and 25 years old. They're almost all males and they look like they're ready to fight. I think they're building an army, I think they want to attack us from the inside. I think they're building an army." This hypothesis, he emphasized&nbsp;Trump, is "interesting". "They don't seem illegal immigrants - it has emphasized - they are building something, they have something in mind. We're gonna end all this stuff. We're not gonna let these people take the cities away and take the country away, it's not gonna happen." Among the applause&nbsp;Trump&nbsp; he announced that, as president of the United States, he will start the "more mass deportation in the history of our country, because this situation is unsustainable. No country can endure such a situation." &nbsp;

